                  <handDesc>
                     <p>The writing is in large rustic capitals of a literary type and very early in form (Sanders). - First hand (l. 1): a nice capital writing, by an expert hand; the other hands show (much) less experience; some are very heavy (l. 3); l. 13-14 are nearly in "capitalis quadrata", but without elegance (Welkenhuysen)</p>
